<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - INSTRUMENTS
        (New Data Link Driven Instrument Cluster) - REMOVE AND INSTALL - SPEEDOMETER SENSOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SPEEDOMETER SENSOR</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Turn the key switch to OFF before removing or installing the speedometer sensor.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the sensor connector from the wiring harness connector (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0815519">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0815519" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0815519" filename="../figg08/G0815519.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Disconnect Sensor Connector From Wiring Harness Connector</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SENSOR BODY</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. LOCKNUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. HOUSING</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. TRANSMISSION SPEEDOMETER GEAR</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. SENSOR CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the sensor locknut and remove the sensor from the back of the transmission
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Allison automatic transmissions use a
                        <emph type="bold">non-adjustable</emph>
                        speedometer sensor, but its electrical operation is similar to the standard International
                        sensor.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new sensor by turning into the housing until it bottoms out against the
                    speedometer gear.
                    <emph type="bold">Back off one (1) turn.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the lock nut using two wrenches to keep the sensor from turning while tightening
                    the locknut. Tighten to 15 ft-lbs. (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the sensor connector to the wiring harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test drive the vehicle to test the speedometer.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
